{
  "circuit": {
    "description": "Varactor reverse-biased: V1=2V drives Varactor cathode through R=10kohm to ground (anode) so V_d < 0. Reverse-bias is the Varactor's documented operating regime (voltage-controlled junction capacitance, Cj=CJO/(1-Vd/VJ)^M). Exercises depletion-cap formula in reverse bias and DIODE_CAP_SCHEMA slots.",
